    "plan_cost_usd": 1.1778267,
    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've created:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `Stepper` Compound Component\n\n### What will be created (4 changes, no existing files modified)\n\n#### 1. `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx` (new file)\nA pure-React compound component with 7 named exports:\n- **Two contexts** (`StepperContext`, `StepperItemContext`) with guard hooks (`useStepper`, `useStepperItem`) — same pattern as `carousel.tsx`\n- **`Stepper`** — `flex flex-col gap-4` container + context provider; `orientation` drives how children style themselves\n- **`StepperItem`** — derives `data-state` (\"completed\"/\"active\"/\"pending\") from `activeStep` vs its `step` prop; provides `StepperItemContext` to children\n- **`StepperTrigger`** — circular `<button>` using `group-data-[state=*]/stepper-item:` selectors for state-based colors; defaults to showing step number\n- **`StepperTitle` / `StepperDescription`** — simple `<p>` wrappers with `data-slot`\n- **`StepperSeparator`** — `flex-1 h-[2px]` (horizontal) or `w-[2px] min-h-8 ml-[15px]` (vertical); turns primary when `activeStep > step`\n- **`StepperContent`** — early-returns `null` when `step !== activeStep` (context-powered)\n\n#### 2. `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx` (new file)\n3-step horizontal demo (\"Account\", \"Profile\", \"Complete\") with `useState`, clickable triggers that jump to any step, `StepperContent` panels, and Previous/Next buttons.\n\n#### 3. `ui/_registry.ts` — append entry\n```ts\n{ name: \"stepper\", type: \"registry:ui\", files: [{ path: \"ui/stepper.tsx\", type: \"registry:ui\" }] }\n```\nInserted alphabetically between \"spinner\" and \"switch\" (no npm dependencies needed).\n\n#### 4. `examples/_registry.ts` — append entry\n```ts\n{ name: \"stepper-demo\", type: \"registry:example\", registryDependencies: [\"stepper\", \"button\"], files: [...] }\n```\nInserted alphabetically between the last \"spinner-*\" entry and \"switch-demo\".",
